         Hmmmmm.</P><P>Potus' suggestion works for me.</P><P>My gear sucks, so when the list was posted, I was pretty happy to see I had a coupla items that had an effect.  (Bracelet of Woven Grass, Dark Circlet, Enshrouded Veil and the 3INT/WIS bracer)  However, I have since discovered that my free bonus type effects allow me to Gate and FD faster!  *Yay*  <i>(A faster FD is no bad thing.  I'll not complain about that one!)</i></P><P>My Enshrouded Veil even has a level three effect that's of absolutely no use to me whatsoever!  <i>(Which is sorta interesting, since an awful lot of Necromancers seems to wear these!)</i>  Frankly, I fail to see why there're two summoning lines at all.  Surely it'd have made far more sense to leave all pet summoning spells as a single category, no?</P><P>My expectation was that the effects <b>would</b> be as Potus describes.  </P><P>I was pretty narked when the focus items first went in, 'cos I let one of the crystal balls with the AfflictionIII effect go for basically nothing recently.  Then again, now I see I'd have had the effect for just a few hours anyhow.</P><P>Anyhow, my vote would definitely go for losing the spell level restrictions and just making each focus tier superior to those below it.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
