        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=37193&amp;TOPIC_ID=4665&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Tweak+suggestion+to+focus+items%2E+Opinions+PLZ&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Someone on 7th server board posted this idea about focus items. My opinion is that it makes too much sense for VI to do it.<BR>Anyway here's the post: </P><P>The following would have been(IMO) a better implementation of the focus effects (and probably would have been somewhat easier to implement):</P><P>SPELL LINES:<BR>Abjuration<BR>Alteration<BR>Conjuration<BR>Divination<BR>Evocation</P><P><BR>FOCUS EFFECTS:<BR>Haste - Affects the time it takes to cast the spell<BR>Efficiency - Affects mana usage<BR>Effectiveness - Affects the damage output,buff stat changes/etc.<BR>Duration - Affects the duration the spell effect lasts (this obviously has no effect on direct damage or any other immediate effect spell types).<BR>Range - Affects the range on spells cast for the associated spell line.<BR>Delivery - Reduces the targets resists against the spell cast.<BR>Mastery - includes ALL of the effects listed above</P><P><BR>I believe the effect percentages below to be reasonable, although alternatively there could be 1-5 levels instead of just 1-3.<BR>Haste %/Focus effect Level = 10%, 20%, 30%<BR>Efficiency %/Focus effect level = 5%, 10%, 15%<BR>Effectiveness %/Focus effect level = 5%, 10%, 15%<BR>Duration %/Focus effect level = 10%, 20%, 30% on beneficial spells (5%, 10%, 15% on DOT and debuff spells)<BR>Range %/Focus effect level = 5%, 10%, 15%<BR>Delivery %/Focus effect level = 5%, 10%, 15%<BR>Mastery %/Focus effect level = (see the individual focus effects)</P><P>A couple focus effect examples under this implementation:<BR>Abjuration Efficiency II - 10% less mana usage on all castable Abjuration based spells.<BR>Evocation Haste I - All evocation based spells cast 10% faster.</P><P>The focus effects should work on all spells of the appropriate spell line no matter what level the spell being cast is. Right click item spells should not be affected.<BR>Only the item with the best focus effect level should be selected for each focus effect type when a relevant spell is cast(similar to melee haste items). All relevant focus effect types(Haste, Efficiency, etc) should be taken into consideration on each spell cast.</P><P>Focus effects should be usable by everyone on all spells, and item "Recommended Levels" could apply to items with the level 2 focus effects. Low level melee haste items are usable by high level characters, so why should low level focus effect items not be?</P><P>Personally I believe coding the reagent conservation effect is a waste of time and it doesn't really make any sense to begin with. If a spell is supposed to use a reagent upon each cast, I see no reason why it shouldn't use that reagent every single time as it is a part of the spell. While I am mentioning reagents...I would love to see different bone chip types used with the necro summon pet spells. War bone chips could summon a tougher pet (maybe add a level or 2 to the normal summoned pet), Ice bone chips could summon a pet that casts the ice DD spell of Ice bone skeletons, and so on. The necro could place the selected bone chip type on the cursor before casting the spell to specifically select a bone chip type.  </P><P></P><P>Viliu Delosmuertos-Ironscale <BR>Steel Thunder - Seventh Hammer<BR>53rd winter</P><P>No I can't give you crack but I can make you dead," Viliu<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
